# Card-audit (mtg-948 Part B): Disenchant — scripted targeted artifact destroy.
#
# Closed issue mtg-498 closed Disenchant as WORKING:
#   A:SP$ Destroy | ValidTgts$ Artifact,Enchantment
#   "{1}{W} Instant — Destroy target artifact or enchantment." (CR 701.7 Destroy).
#
# Wave 1 left it skeleton/heuristic-only. This puzzle scripts P0 casting
# Disenchant at P1's Mox Jet (a vanilla artifact: mana ability only, no ETB or
# trigger), proving the Artifact target restriction is honored and the artifact
# is destroyed into its owner's graveyard.
#
# Scenario:
#   - P0: Disenchant in hand, 1 Plains + 1 generic land (Forest) to pay {1}{W}.
#   - P1: a Mox Jet on the battlefield (the artifact target).
#   - Script: P0 casts Disenchant targeting the Mox Jet -> it is destroyed.

[metadata]
Name:Card Audit - Disenchant Destroys an Artifact
Goal:Win
Turns:1
Difficulty:Easy
Description:P0 scripts Disenchant ({1}{W}) onto P1's Mox Jet, destroying the artifact into P1's graveyard. Backs the targeted-destroy aspect of issue mtg-498 (SP$ Destroy, ValidTgts$ Artifact,Enchantment; CR 701.7).

[state]
turn=1
activeplayer=p0
activephase=MAIN1
p0life=20
p0hand=Disenchant
p0battlefield=Plains;Forest
p0library=Forest;Forest;Forest;Forest;Forest

p1life=20
p1battlefield=Mox Jet
p1library=Mountain;Mountain;Mountain;Mountain;Mountain

[p0_script]
# Destroy P1's Mox Jet. The `targeting` clause names the artifact semantically.
cast Disenchant targeting Mox Jet

[assertions]
# Disenchant was actually cast.
spell cast Disenchant
# The Mox Jet was destroyed into P1's graveyard (CR 701.7). This is durable:
# it holds at game end even though the heuristic plays lands onto P1's
# battlefield in later turns.
opponent graveyard contains Mox Jet
# Disenchant itself resolved into P0's graveyard.
me graveyard contains Disenchant
# mtg-961 note: the `creature died` event was widened to fire for ALL creature
# deaths (destroy/sacrifice/SBA), not just lethal damage — see the Wrath of God
# and Royal Assassin audit puzzles, which now assert it directly. We do NOT add
# a `creature died` assertion HERE on purpose: Mox Jet is an ARTIFACT, not a
# creature, so CreatureDied correctly does not fire for its destruction. The
# `move_card` chokepoint emits CreatureDied only for objects that `is_creature()`
# at the moment they leave the battlefield — destroying a non-creature artifact
# must stay silent on that event. The destruction is verified by graveyard-contains.
